text: Independents took all bar one of the seats, securing them an overall majority Elections to the Badenoch and Strathspey District Council took place in May 1988, alongside elections to the councils of Scotland's various other districts. The number of seats and the total vote share won by each party is listed below. Voter turnout was 44.0%. ==References== Category:1988 Scottish local elections
title: 1988 Badenoch and Strathspey District Council election
